# Frontend conventions

- Client pages that stream scans use `"use client"`, `api` from `lib/api.ts`, and WebSocket `${WS_URL}/ws/scans/{id}`.
- Reuse `FindingsTable`, `ProgressPanel`, `SeverityBadge` / `StatusBadge` instead of reinventing.
- Attack Mode form: vector checkboxes, optional auth header, delay/threads, authorization confirm checkbox before launch.
- Finding PoC: copy-to-clipboard for `poc_curl` / request / response; link to `/history/[scanId]/findings/[findingId]` for detail.
- Keep the existing visual language (display + mono fonts, signal accent, fog backgrounds). Avoid dark-mode purple AI defaults.
- Report downloads: open/fetch `/api/scans/{id}/report?format=json|html` via the API URL.
- Phase 4 pages: `/login`, `/api-mode`, `/templates`, `/frida`. Attach Bearer token via `getToken()` in `lib/api.ts` when auth is enabled.
